<p>Always link the button to the most relevant page. Do not send every post to your homepage.</p>
<h3>Writing Tips That Increase Clicks</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Start with a number.</strong> "5 signs your AC needs repair" outperforms "Is your AC broken?"</li>
<li><strong>Add urgency.</strong> "Offer ends Friday" or "3 spots remaining" drives action.</li>
<li><strong>Name the benefit.</strong> "Save 2 hours" beats "convenient service."</li>
<li><strong>Ask a question.</strong> Posts that open with a question get higher read-through rates.</li>
</ul>
<p>Add UTM parameters to your CTA links so you can track post-driven traffic in <a href="/blog/google-analytics-4-setup/">Google Analytics 4</a>.</p>
