<h3>The 7-Day Visibility Window</h3>
<p>Update posts remain accessible for up to 6 months but lose prominence after roughly 7 days. Google prioritizes recent content. A weekly posting schedule ensures you always have a fresh post in the priority position.</p>
<h3>Quality Over Quantity</h3>
<p>Posting 3 times per week with generic content does less than posting once per week with specific, valuable updates. A <a href="/blog/create-content-calendar-seo/">content calendar</a> helps you plan GBP posts alongside your blog and social media.</p>
<p>Consistency matters more than volume. Give it 60-90 days of consistent posting before evaluating results. The data on <a href="/blog/how-long-seo-takes/">how long SEO takes</a> applies here too.</p>
